getFeatureIterator

IFeatureIterator getFeatureIterator(java.lang.String[] fields,
                                    IProjection newProjection)
                                    throws ReadDriverException
Returns an iterator over all the features of the vectorial data source. It applies a relational algebra "projection" operator (selects the specified fields). It the param newProjection is not null, it reprojects all the returned features to this projection

Parameters:
fields - fields we are intested in of the data source
Returns:
feature iterator whose features has as attributes the specified fields
Throws:
ReadDriverException

getFeatureIterator

IFeatureIterator getFeatureIterator(java.lang.String sql,
                                    IProjection newProjection)
                                    throws ReadDriverException
Return a feature iterator from a given sql statement.
In this case, the statement will have the "projection" operator (select campo1, campo2, ...etc) and the "selection" operator (where ....)

Parameters:
sql - statement which define a filter. SQL sintax is very extrict, and must be suported by GDBMS
newProjection - new projection for the returned features (if not null)
Returns:
feature iterator
Throws:
ReadDriverException

getFeatureIterator

IFeatureIterator getFeatureIterator(java.awt.geom.Rectangle2D rect,
                                    java.lang.String[] fields,
                                    IProjection newProjection,
                                    boolean fastResult)
                                    throws ReadDriverException
Makes an spatial query returning a feature iterator over the features which intersects or are contained in the rectangle query. Applies a restriction to the alphanumeric fields returned by the iterator, and a reprojection.
Details:
  • If newProjection is null, rect Rectangle2D is consideered in the same projection that the source data.
  • If newProjection is not null, Rectangle2D is consideered in this projection (newProjection). So the source driver must reproject this rectangle before to make the query, and after that reproject all the returned features' geometry

Parameters:
rect -
fields -
Returns:
Throws:
ReadDriverException
